Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or advanced diabetic nephropathy. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Liver enzymes and electrolytes are within normal limits. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment of underlying etiology.
